						<summary>

						<p>On the Dhavajastaṁbha in front of the Kēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>Mādirāja, son of Rāmayadēva Chōḍa mahārāja.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 1353 (wrong for 1351), <hi rend="italic">Saumya, Vaiśākha,</hi> śu. [5] Thursday, corresponding to 1429 A.D., April 8 (Friday). In the third face, the record refers to a chronogram: <hi rend="italic">dvaya-śara-trīndu</hi> denoting Śaka 1352.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the erection of a pillar by the chief in front of the temple of Aśvatthanārāyaṇa of Niḍiṁgallu.</p>						

						</summary>
